**Answer:** At Mn_1.10, Manu offers this etymology: the waters are called *nāraḥ* (plural of *nāra*) because they are the sons of Nara (the primordial Male Spirit). Since those waters were his first dwelling place (*ayana*), the Supreme Being is called **Nārāyaṇa** — "he whose first abode was the waters." The name thus parses as *nāra* (waters/sons of Nara) + *ayana* (abode/dwelling place).
